<br>
Still, entirely IC I don't think there's anything silly about romance, whether it's actually acted out or just implied.  Marriage is still a very important part of a person's life (both IC and IRL), and can add a lot of depth to a person's character.  Even when Tallonar's not around (in which case there's no 'romance' going on) his very existence affects Didi.  How she talks about him, what she does (e.g. go hunting for smithing supplies) for him, whether she remains faithful to him, those things are all things that define her character, both for me and for other people.  And they're quite independent of any elements of 'romance'.<br>
<br>
And I still maintain that whether or not people get distracted during the hunt has nothing to do with whether RP marriage is silly.  Getting distracted during the hunt is silly, end of story.  Whether it's because of a RP marriage or because you're shopping in the market channel, it's equally silly.  (With the exception of RL priorities, as Caillou says.)<br>
<br>
I don't really see how you could develop a well-rounded character will much depth to him without at least considering your relationship to Mrs. Siffo.  In fact, the very fact that you say there IS a Mrs. Siffo and that she affect your behaviour (you're faithful to her) means that yes, Siffo, you too are RP'ing marriage.  So Mrs. Siffo isn't going to distract you with tells, because she doesn't have a player behind her ... so what?  You're still RP'ing that you're married, and you behaviour is still being defined by your relationship to her.  =)  So nyah.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><table border=0><tr><td width=20%><img src="http://users.bigpond.net.au/stbt/didi/a_didisig.gif" height=120 width=120></td><td><FONT FACE="Tempus Sans ITC" SIZE="2">
